p: The total number of participants in the study was 184, which included 132 subjects who tested positive at screening and 52 out of 2,526 people who tested negative upon screening and went on to test positive at the end of quarantine. Most of the subjects had asymptomatic infection ( n = 145, 78.8%) and were females ( n = 115, 62.5%). The number of subjects progressively increased across increasing age categories, with 22.3% ( n = 41) of the subjects being in the â‰¥60 years category.
